Project Snapshot — Active Narrative Threads and Concrete Plot Points

Theme: Tighten the loop between intent, effect, and accountability. Three fronts: (A) TUI must keep users in flow; (B) `--save` must produce a truthful, composable commit; (C) Tooling must be auditable, reversible, and safe by default.

Thread A — TUI editing and responsiveness
Conflict: Editing kicks users out and status rendering leaves artifacts; scrolling exceeds bounds; shell args to $EDITOR are brittle.

Scenes (code-bound):
- App lifecycle keeps editor round-trips inside the TUI
  • tui/src/lib.rs::App::enter_directory(): stop terminating after edit; wrap editor launch with disable_raw_mode + LeaveAlternateScreen, then EnterAlternateScreen + enable_raw_mode; on success reload selection/preview; on error, show concise message in preview.
- Editor writes back to original file
  • tui/src/lib.rs::user_editor(original_path, contents) -> io::Result<()>: write contents to temp, launch $EDITOR using Shell::get_interactive_args() (no extra "-c"), on exit write temp back to original_path.
- Clean status line rendering
  • tui/src/lib.rs::display_status(): replace carriage-return hack with crossterm::execute!(MoveToColumn(0), Clear(ClearType::CurrentLine)) before drawing spinner/message.
- In-app edit + navigation discipline
  • tui/src/lib.rs::list_tui(): bind 'e' to edit selected file; add Home/End; PageUp/PageDown scroll by visible_height-1; cap scroll to file_lines.saturating_sub(visible_height).
- Focused TODO browsing and defaults
  • tui/src/lib.rs::App::refresh_files(): when in TODO dir (VIZIER_TODO_DIR or .vizier/todos), include only *.md, ignore dotfiles.
- Cross-shell editor args fixed
  • tui/src/lib.rs::user_editor(): rely entirely on Shell::get_interactive_args() to include command flag; do not append another "-c".
- Events pane + durable errors
  • tui/src/lib.rs: Add App.errors deque, render bottom "Events" pane with last 3 entries; colorize Error:/Warn:; append JSONL to .vizier/logs/errors.jsonl on failures.
- Chat-visible Assistant error frames
  • tui/src/chat.rs: On Err from prompt_with_tools_and_status, push Assistant message starting with "Error:" and log to errors.jsonl with correlation_id.
- SAFE_APPLY banner
  • tui/src/chat.rs: When SAFE_APPLY not set, show yellow banner "Dry-run: tools not executed. Set SAFE_APPLY=1 to apply." once per session and after plan-only turns.

Acceptance:
- Edit returns to TUI with changes saved and preview updated; spinner has no artifacts; scroll bounds enforced; 'e' edits selected TODO; editor works across Bash/Zsh/Fish; errors surface inline and into .vizier/logs/errors.jsonl.

Thread B — Version-control composability for --save
Conflict: Commit messages were based on stale diffs; help text mismatched flags; first-run status storage brittle.

Scenes (code-bound):
- Commit from final, staged diff
  • cli/src/main.rs (args.save): compute prompts::tools::diff() after LLM updates and after `git add -u`.
- Single, testable save flow
  • cli/src/main.rs: extract fn save_project() -> Result<(), Box<dyn Error>> performing: (a) LLM snapshot/TODO updates, (b) git add -u, (c) recompute diff, (d) build commit msg, (e) git commit.
- Help text parity
  • cli/src/main.rs::print_usage(): show -S/--summarize and -s/--save correctly.
- First-run robustness for status store
  • prompts/src/tools.rs::load_todos(): create .vizier/ and empty todos.json if missing; return Ok(empty map).

Acceptance:
- --save commit message reflects all staged changes including .vizier updates; help flags match; save_project() returns errors; status updates work without preexisting todos.json.

Thread C — Safety rails, observability, and reversible effects
Conflict: Tool execution is opaque; users can’t link conversations to commits; failures lack durable context.

Scenes (code-bound):
- Conversation/LLM audit stream
  • prompts/src/lib.rs, prompts/src/tools.rs, tui/src/chat.rs: add Audit handle + FileAuditSink to append JSONL events (user/assistant/tool/error) to .vizier/logs/llm_audit.jsonl with token counts and correlation ids.
- Plan capture + SAFE_APPLY gate
  • prompts/src/lib.rs: persist execution plans to .vizier/logs/plan.jsonl; if SAFE_APPLY not set, return dry-run summary; when set, execute and record outcomes.
- Error surfacing and event tracing
  • tui/src/chat.rs, tui/src/lib.rs: render Assistant "Error:" frames; bottom Events pane; write .vizier/logs/errors.jsonl with correlation ids.
- Bootstrap status store
  • prompts/src/tools.rs::load_todos(): ensure .vizier/ exists and todos.json initialized on first use.
- Git linkage for audits (anchor + notes)
  • cli/src/main.rs, prompts/src/file_tracking.rs: compute Audit-Anchor from staged state; include trailer in commit, emit CommitLink/CommitCreated events, and write git notes for JSONL ranges.

Acceptance:
- Every tool call logs an audit event; SAFE_APPLY allows dry-run; errors get logged and surfaced; fresh repos don’t crash; commits carry Audit-Anchor linking to session logs.

What changed in this snapshot:
- Thread C’s error surfacing scenes consolidated into TUI Events pane + Assistant error frames + durable errors.jsonl and correlation ids.
- Marked duplicate TODOs for merge/removal to avoid parallel narratives.

